rComments: Easily one of my favourite profs. Lecture notes are clear and complete. Weekly quiz really help to stay on top of the material. Really cares for the success of his students. Put in a couple of hours weekly and the exams wont feel like a mountain.

This is one of the greatest profs at uOttawa. He really cares about his students and will always be open to stop teaching to answer questions. Exams are pretty tough but if you listen to examples and practice, you'll be fine. Definitely take him if you can!!

Took mechanics 2 from him and now thermo. Hands down one of the best profs in MCG. He's teaching via writing and sketching on his tablet which is excellent. Quizzes, midterm, final are pretty straightforward if you do the practise problems. IMO, waay better than Hallett in terms of difficulty of the exams and course delivery. Excellent choice!

By far the best and kindest prof I had so far. His lectures are very concise and organized and he thoroughly explains everything. Very assessable outside of class and replies quickly to emails. His quizzes, tutorials and midterm were very fair and reflective of what was learned in class, no surprises. He truly cares about his students.

Amazing prof, tells you exactly what he wants, midterm very accurately reflects what he taught in class. He cares about his students and always replies to emails promptly. One thing, he does take what he says seriously, so pay attention to his emails/announcements. After having Hallett online, he's a king fr. Pro tip: focus on special cases!

He's an excellent prof! He does his best to help you with anything. The way he teaches via drawing sketch to his tablet is just awesome and helps you understand much better. Even though, the course gets a little difficult towards the end, exams are straightforward, just practice with the questions he posts and you should be fine.
He is a gem. Cares about students and very accessible outside the class.
Ce prof est vraiment génial, ses notes de cours sont très faciles à suivre et ses tests n'ont aucune surprises mais sont quand même rigoureux. Taking his class has been a pleasure.

Of all the profs I had, Richer made the most efforts to make the transition to online classes go as smoothly as possible. His notes are very clear and quizzes reflect exactly what will be evaluated on exams. If you listen in class and take the quizzes and homework seriously, it's impossible to do badly in Richer's class.
what is there to say, one of the best profs I've had in 3 years of engineering classes

I had Prof. Richer for Thermo and he is the best professor I have ever had. His lectures (even though he gets you to write a lot) are very thorough and clear. He also gives a lot of sample problems and is ready to meet with you and explain anything you did not understand. Best Prof Ever !
Lectures are super detailed. Quizzes and tutorials are graded so force you to keep up to date every week which is easy if you attend all the lectures
Probably best MCG at UOttawa

Hands down one of the best profs you can get especially for a difficult class like mechanics 2. His notes and problem solutions are extremely clear and I find myself using some of his writing methods still to this day in the classes that apply. There's honestly nothing he could've done better to teach that class.

His teaching method is more old school, which I personally prefer. He writes the notes and examples on the black board, so it's easier to understand when he goes through every step of the problem. His quizzes are very easy, if you do some practice problems before, and his exams are easy if you study hard enough. He also answers every question well.
Great professor!
He's sooooooo nice and good. Honestly the best prof I ever had. Best notes and always there to help.
teacherRatingTags: ['Beware of pop quizzes', 'Gives good feedback', 'Amazing lectures ']

rComments: great prof. super organized but his tests are really long(and cover all the material).
Great professor. would recommend it
Amazing Professor!
Overall good prof. Could do more examples in class to clarify the content though.
Amazing professor. His lectures are clear and to the point making it easy to understand the material. He's one of the best profs I've ever had. I wish he could teach my other classes.

Incredible prof! Lectures and notes are very clear and easy to follow/understand. He's always ready to help. You're in luck if he's your prof! The DGD quizzes were a bit annoying, but he teaches so well that they never were a problem, they actually helpedget more practice in oftentimes.

Dr. Richer has a fantastic way of teaching that is incredibly clear and precise. Some may find lectures a bit dry as a result, but lecture notes are top notch and very easy to review with. It is sometimes difficult to keep up and do well on weekly quizzes and the marking scheme is frustrating at times. Overall, Dr. Richer is top notch.

If you want to pass Thermodynamics with flying colors, you ABSOLUTELY MUST take it with Dr. Richer.  His notes are crystal clear and will definitely help you to understand and learn Thermo in a clear and structured way. Attend EVERY class and ask if you don't know something. Practice his suggested problems, read his notes and you'll pass.

This course is said to be on the more difficult side, however Richer really breaks it down for you and gives you a step by step method. Once you've mastered the method, the course is a breeze. I guess the only bad thing I can say here that the midterm was a little too long (3 questions) for 80 mins.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Beware of pop quizzes', 'Lecture heavy']

rComments: good
Attend class and do your homework and you'll do really well. Some questions on the final exam were the same as textbook practice examples.
HE'S GOOD! WOULD TAKE AGAIN!

I would recommend taking Thermo I with him if possible. He writes his notes on the board at an easy-going pace and has very detailed solutions to problems that are directly reflected on the exams. He has an expected "methodology" to solving problems that has a very logical flow, but expect to lose marks if you don't follow it to a T.
EASY FINAL!!

Great prof, I went to every single class just for the notes. Quizzes are reaaaly easy, the only tricky problems you'll ever encounter will be during DGD's when the T.A is helping out. Practice a few of the harder problems and read notes, and you're good.
Amazing prof! but you have to go to his lecture to keep notes since he won't put them online. However, he would put key notes on bb. His course is really clarified.

Amazing prof, I literally think he is the perfect professor! Amazing spoken french, clear and detailed notes, tests are hard but hey, it's thermodynamics... Makes sure you understand. He is always at his office hours on time.  If he could teach me all the way through my degree, I would be very happy (and smarter)!

Engineering mechanics is a hard course, so you should definitely go to all of your lectures! Patrick Richer is a new professor and is amazing!! He is very clear, he takes it slow and makes sure everyone understands. His exams were hard but resembled some of the difficult textbook questions. If you attend his lectures and office hours, you'll pass!
He may be new, but he is the master of hand-written notes. It's obvious he is an expert in thermal coatings. He does whatever it takes to make students understand the basics.
Best pro ever

The words amazingly fantastic come to mind. He can express his expectations as well as the content of the course effectively :)  "Ummmmm sir, why is there a C behind the degree sign?" - student in mechanics course doing a problem with angles.   "Haha oh, that's because it's the morning." - Patrick thinking he was teaching his thermo class.
Unreal prof. Listen, learn and do well.

Writes all his notes out on the board so it gives you tons of time to copy them. Gives out a lot of examples and posts solutions to every recommended problem on blackboard.  The DGD's are mandatory as the TA always gives out questions for you to do and they are graded. Midterm wasn't that hard and part marks are a life saver. Study and you'll pass.
OMG, you wanna pass this course???? u need to take it with this guy, his amazing, he made me love forces and i never did before....
Great Prof, if something is unclear will for sure help you out, also give lots of help options
Amazing professor
